1. *Mač* je bio glavno oružje vitezova. (The sword was the main weapon of the knights.)
2. *Mač* je oštar kao brijač. (The sword is sharp as a razor.)
3. Ratnik je zasjao *mač*em u ruci. (The warrior shone with a sword in his hand.)
4. *Mač*eva oštrica je izrađena od kvalitetnog čelika. (The sword blade is made of high-quality steel.)
5. Kralj je udario svojim *mač*em po stolu. (The king hit the table with his sword.)
6. Stari *mač*evi su često ukrašavani zlatom i dragim kamenjem. (Old swords are often decorated with gold and precious stones.)
7. Kovač je izvukao *mač* iz peći i počeo da ga kuje. (The blacksmith pulled the sword out of the furnace and started to forge it.)
8. *Mač* je pao na zemlju kada se borac srušio. (The sword fell to the ground when the fighter collapsed.)
9. Vitez je držao svoj *mač* čvrsto u ruci dok je napadao neprijatelja. (The knight held his sword firmly in his hand while attacking the enemy.)
10. Na dnu jezera pronađen je *mač* koji datira iz srednjeg veka. (A sword dating back to the Middle Ages was found at the bottom of the lake.)

Note: In Serbian, the word "mač" can be translated to "sword" in English.